<button class="accordion">What is a senior staff nurse?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>A senior staff nurse in the UK is the nurse who is in the middle of ward hierarchy, above staff nurses but below charge nurses and ward managers or old sisters. 
Senior nurses perform many of the same tasks as staff nurses but are in authority when they are in charge of the ward or department area during a shift.</p>
