<button class="accordion">How much does a staff nurse earn in the UK?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>An early career staff nurse with 1-4 years of experience earns an average total compensation of £24,045 based on 894 salaries. A mid-career staff nurse with 5-9 years of experience earns an average full wage of £26,748 based on 384 salaries.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is a level 1 nurse?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The level 1 registered nurse, under the direction of the nurse manager, is accountable for the provision of direct care to assigned patients. The Level 1 registered nurse contributes to unit activities and supports the enhancement of the care delivery system at the unit level.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What's the lowest level of nursing?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>As the name suggests, certified nursing assistants or CNAs assist nurses with patient admittance and vitals. It is the lowest-level credential related to the nursing field and the quickest point of entry. It is important to remember that CNAs are not technically nurses.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is the role of a senior charge nurse?</button>
